Sentencas: The composites of Ni-Cu oxides with gadolinium doped ceria (GDC) are emerging as highly proficient anode catalysts, owing to their remarkable performance for solid oxide fuel cells operated with biogas.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this context, the nanocomposite catalysts (1 - x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC (x = 0.2-0.8; y = 1,1.3) are synthesized using a solid-state reaction route.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cubic and monoclinic structures are observed for NiO and CuO phases, respectively, while CeO2 showed cubic fluorite structure.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The scanning electron microscopic images revealed a rise in the particle size with an increase in the copper and GDC concentration.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The optical band gap values are calculated in the range 2.82-2.33 eV from UV-visible analysis.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Raman spectra confirmed the presence of vibration modes of CeO2 and NiO.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the nanocomposite anodes is increased as the concentration of copper and GDC increased and reached at 9.48 S cm(-1) for 0.2NiO-0.8CuO/1.3GDC composition at 650 degrees
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: C. The electrochemical performance of (1 - x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC (x = 0.2-0.8; y = 1,1.3)-based fuel cells is investigated with biogas fuel at 650 degrees C. Among all of the as-synthesized anodes, the fuel cell with composition 0.2NiO-0.8CuO/1.3GDC showed the best performance, such as an open circuit voltage of 0.84 V and peak power density of 72 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, from these findings, it can be inferred that among all other compositions, the 0.2NiO-0.8CuO/1.3GDC anode is a superior combination for the high electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells fueled with biogas.
Titulo: Nanocomposite Catalyst (1-x)NiO-xCuO/yGDC for Biogas Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
